         <abstract>
            <p>For $\lambda &gt; 0$ and $k \geqslant 0$ we present a method which permits us to obtain inequalities of the type $(k + \alpha)^{\lambda - 1} &lt; \Gamma(k + \lambda)/\Gamma(k + 1) &lt; (k + \beta)^{\lambda - 1}$, with the usual notation for the gamma function, where $\alpha$ and $\beta$ are independent of $k$. Some examples are also given which improve well-known inequalities. Finally, we are also able to show in some cases that the values $\alpha$ and $\beta$ in the inequalities that we obtain cannot be improved.</p>
          </abstract>
